epublican\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |105,088\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |38%\n|-\n|[[2002 United States Senate election in Delaware|2002]]\n|General\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |135,253\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |58%\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Raymond J. Clatworthy\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |94,793\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |41%\n|-\n|[[2008 United States Senate election in Delaware|2008]]\n|General\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |257,484\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |65%\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |[[Christine O'Donnell]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |140,584\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |35%\n|-\n|[[2008 United States presidential election|2008]]\n|rowspan=2|Vice President\n|General\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |69,498,516<br/>365 electoral votes (270 needed)\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |53%\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |[[Sarah Palin]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |59,948,323<br/>173 electoral votes\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |46%\n|-\n|[[2012 United States presidential election|2012]]\n|General\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |65,915,796<br/>332 electoral votes (270 needed)\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |51%\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |[[Paul Ryan]]\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |60,933,500<br/>206 electoral votes\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |47%\n|}\n\n== Writings by Biden ==\n\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/Hague-Convention-International-Child-Abduction/dp/0756722500|title=Hague Convention On International Child Abduction: Applicable Law And Institutional Framework Within Certain Convention Countries Report To The Senate |last=Biden |first=Joseph R., Jr. |date=April 1, 2000|publisher=Diane Publishing|isbn=0-7567-2250-0|author2=Jesse Helms|author2-link=Jesse Helms}}\n* {{Cite book|url=http://frwebgate.acce